{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "f1e2d3c4-bd-cache-bajaj-plaintext-2026",
    "name": "Bureau / Dedupe Caching Service",
    "description": "Send the request body as plain JSON (`ProcessRequest`). The collection-level pre-request script encrypts it and wraps it in the envelope, then the test script decrypts the response and shows the inner ProcessResponse.\n\n## How to use\n\n1. Pick a request (Process - Bureau / Process - Dedupe / Process - Invalid / Stub - Bureau / Stub - Dedupe).\n2. Edit the Body tab as **normal JSON**:\n   ```json\n   {\n     \"config\": { \"serviceName\": \"Bureau\", \"requestId\": \"REQ-1\" },\n     \"data\":   { \"firstName\": \"Krishna\", \"lastName\": \"Vamsi\" }\n   }\n   ```\n3. Hit Send.\n4. Check the **Test Results** tab for the decrypted response, or open the Postman Console (View -> Show Postman Console) to see both the encrypted envelope sent and the plaintext response received.\n\n## What the scripts do\n\n- **Pre-request (collection-level):** for `/api/v1/process`, `/stub/bureau`, and `/stub/dedupe`, reads your raw body, AES-CBC-encrypts it (with the `+` -> `~` swap), and replaces the body with `{ request, reference_id, source_system }` envelope.\n- **Test (collection-level):** parses the envelope response, decrypts `response` if present, asserts the inner shape, and stores the plaintext in `lastDecryptedResponse`.\n\n## Variables\n\n| Variable        | Purpose                              | Default                            |\n|-----------------|--------------------------------------|------------------------------------|\n| `baseUrl`       | Service base URL                     | `http://localhost:8080`            |\n| `aesKey`        | AES-256 key (32 bytes)               | server default                     |\n| `aesIv`         | AES IV (16 bytes)                    | server default                     |\n| `referenceId`   | `reference_id` placed in envelope    | `REF-001`                          |\n| `sourceSystem`  | `source_system` placed in envelope   | `POSTMAN`                          |\n| `lastDecryptedResponse` | Filled by tests (read-only)  |                                    |\n",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "baseUrl",       "value": "http://localhost:8080",                        "type": "string" },
    { "key": "aesKey",        "value": ")H@McQfTjWnZr4u7x!A&C*F-JaNdRgUk",              "type": "string" },
    { "key": "aesIv",         "value": "w9z$C&F)J@NcRfUj",                              "type": "string" },
    { "key": "referenceId",   "value": "REF-001",                                       "type": "string" },
    { "key": "sourceSystem",  "value": "POSTMAN",                                       "type": "string" },
    { "key": "lastDecryptedResponse", "value": "",                                      "type": "string" }
  ],
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Collection-level pre-request: take the plaintext JSON body the user typed,",
          "// AES-CBC encrypt it, and replace the body with the encrypted envelope.",
          "",
          "const url = pm.request.url.toString();",
          "const shouldEncrypt = ['/api/v1/service', '/stub/bureau', '/stub/dedupe'].some(p => url.includes(p));",
          "if (!shouldEncrypt) {",
          "    return;",
          "}",
          "",
          "const rawBody = pm.request.body && pm.request.body.raw;",
          "if (!rawBody || !rawBody.trim()) {",
          "    console.warn('[pre-request] body is empty - nothing to encrypt');",
          "    return;",
          "}",
          "",
          "// Validate JSON early so we get a clean error instead of garbage ciphertext.",
          "try { JSON.parse(rawBody); }",
          "catch (e) { throw new Error('Request body is not valid JSON: ' + e.message); }",
          "",
          "const key = CryptoJS.enc.Utf8.parse(pm.collectionVariables.get('aesKey'));",
          "const iv  = CryptoJS.enc.Utf8.parse(pm.collectionVariables.get('aesIv'));",
          "",
          "const plaintext = rawBody.replace(/\\+/g, '~');",
          "const ciphertext = CryptoJS.AES.encrypt(",
          "    CryptoJS.enc.Utf8.parse(plaintext),",
          "    key,",
          "    { iv: iv, mode: CryptoJS.mode.CBC, padding: CryptoJS.pad.Pkcs7 }",
          ").toString();",
          "",
          "const envelope = {",
          "    request:       ciphertext,",
          "    reference_id:  pm.collectionVariables.get('referenceId')  || ('REF-' + Date.now()),",
          "    source_system: pm.collectionVariables.get('sourceSystem') || 'POSTMAN'",
          "};",
          "",
          "pm.collectionVariables.set('lastPlaintextRequest', rawBody);",
          "pm.request.body.raw = JSON.stringify(envelope);",
          "",
          "console.log('[pre-request] plaintext  =', rawBody);",
          "console.log('[pre-request] envelope   =', envelope);"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "listen": "test",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Collection-level test: validate envelope shape, decrypt `response` if present.",
          "",
          "let json;",
          "try { json = pm.response.json(); }",
          "catch (e) { throw new Error('Response is not valid JSON: ' + pm.response.text()); }",
          "",
          "pm.test('envelope has status_code + message', function () {",
          "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('status_code');",
          "    pm.expect(json).to.have.property('message');",
          "});",
          "",
          "if (json.response) {",
          "    const key = CryptoJS.enc.Utf8.parse(pm.collectionVariables.get('aesKey'));",
          "    const iv  = CryptoJS.enc.Utf8.parse(pm.collectionVariables.get('aesIv'));",
          "    const ct  = json.response.replace(/~/g, '+');",
          "",
          "    const plaintext = CryptoJS.AES.decrypt(",
          "        ct, key, { iv: iv, mode: CryptoJS.mode.CBC, padding: CryptoJS.pad.Pkcs7 }",
          "    ).toString(CryptoJS.enc.Utf8);",
          "",
          "    pm.collectionVariables.set('lastDecryptedResponse', plaintext);",
          "    console.log('[test] decrypted =', plaintext);",
          "",
          "    pm.test('decrypted response is JSON with config + data', function () {",
          "        const inner = JSON.parse(plaintext);",
          "        pm.expect(inner).to.have.property('config');",
          "        pm.expect(inner).to.have.property('data');",
          "    });",
          "",
          "    pm.test('status_code is 200 and bre_tat ends with ms', function () {",
          "        pm.expect(json.status_code).to.eql('200');",
          "        pm.expect(json.bre_tat).to.match(/^\\d+ms$/);",
          "    });",
          "} else {",
          "    pm.test('error envelope has non-200 status_code', function () {",
          "        pm.expect(json.status_code).to.not.eql('200');",
          "    });",
          "    console.warn('[test] error envelope =', json);",
          "}"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Process - Bureau (plaintext body)",
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }
        ],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/api/v1/service",
          "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
          "path": ["api", "v1", "service"]
        },
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"config\": {\n    \"serviceName\":     \"Bureau\",\n    \"orgName\":         \"B2C\",\n    \"channelName\":     \"SFDC\",\n    \"productName\":     \"PL\",\n    \"requestId\":       \"REQ-001\",\n    \"caseId\":          \"CASE-1001\",\n    \"requestedVersion\":\"v1\"\n  },\n  \"data\": {\n    \"firstName\":   \"Krishna\",\n    \"lastName\":    \"Vamsi\",\n    \"pan\":         \"ABCDE1234F\",\n    \"mobile\":      \"9999999999\",\n    \"dateOfBirth\": \"1990-01-01\"\n  }\n}",
          "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
        },
        "description": "Edit the body as plain JSON. The pre-request script will encrypt it and wrap it in the envelope before sending."
      }
    },
